Liveaboard Scuba Diving Pack List
Based on 2 People, 7 Days
Dress is very casual, and traveling light is recommended.
Pack in soft-sided luggage

Pack in Carry-On

Regulator with octo and submersible pressure gauge
Camera
Film or data storage cards
Batteries
Dive lights
Power block (charging)
Tablet computer with a couple of good books loaded
Dive computers with depth gauge
Passports, valid for at least 180 days beyond period of intended stay
Flight tickets
Liveabord reservation information
Hotel reservation information
Transfer reservation information
Shore excursion information
Visa, if needed
Trip insurance policy info and contact info
Diving insurance policy info and contact info
Health insurance policy info and contact info
Wallet
Cash for tips, transfers, and exit fees
Earbuds
Earplugs for sound
Earplanes for pressure changes
Cell phone

Scuba Gear

Masks
Fins
Snorkels
SMBs and reels
Buoyancy compensators
Wetsuits warm enough for making numerous dives
Diving waivers
Health forms
Certification cards and Nitrox cards

Misc

Dive camera housing
Travel power strip
Dive training manual
Wash-in-sink detergent packs in zip-lock bag
Travel clothesline
Immodium AD
Broad spectrum antibiotic, if your doctor will prescribe one
Tylenol
Ibuprofen
Lots of sunscreen in zip-lock bags
A pack of flushable wipes
Bonine for seasickness
Large trash bag, folded
Chargers for cell phone, tablet

Clothing and Personal Items for Her

Note: in some places it's inappropriate for women to wear short shorts or mini skirts in public
For the airplane trips: 1 pair of long pants, 2 pairs of socks, comfortable but light walking shoes
Shoes for wearing on the boat, in a bag
Light jacket
Sun hat
Sunglasses
2 swimsuits
3 light UV-protective shirts
3 light UV-protective pants or shorts
3 light tops for dinners
2 bras that match the tops
1 skirt or pair of pants for dinners
1 pair of underwear per day
Enough prescription medication for your entire stay, in zip-lock bag
2 Buffs for hair
Lightweight sleeping clothes, 3
Tampons, maxi pads and pantiliners (including extras)
Tolietries for showers and shaving, in zip-lock bag
Toothbrush, toothpaste, hairbrush, in zip-lock bag
Glasses, extra contacts, contact solution, in zip-lock bag

Clothing and Personal Items for Him

For the airplane trips: 1 pair of long pants, 2 pairs of socks, comfortable but light walking shoes
Shoes for wearing on the boat, in a bag
Light jacket
Sun hat
Sunglasses
2 swimsuits
3 light UV-protective shirts
3 light UV-protective pants or shorts
3 light tops for dinners
1 pair of pants for dinners
1 pair of underwear per day
Enough prescription medication for your entire stay, in zip-lock bag
2 Buffs for Hair
Lightweight sleeping clothes, 3
Tolietries for showers and shaving, in zip-lock bag
Toothbrush, toothpaste, hairbrush, in zip-lock bag
Glasses, extra contacts, contact solution, in zip-lock bag

What NOT to Bring

Tanks
Weights
Towels (assuming the ship provides them)
Hairdryer
Illegal drugs
Makeup
Expensive computer

Before You Go

Leave emergency contact info and travel plans with friends and family.

